Manage Security

Configure key-named authentication as root & allow ssh root access
Generate ssh key on node1, ans setup key-based authentication for the root user
	ssh-keygen
	ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub root@ip address
	
Enable ssh root login and test your configuration
	vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config
	set PermitRootLogin yes
	systemctl restart sshd


HTTPD Server troubleshooting SELinux
The web server on node1 (182.168.70.10) is listening on port 85, ensure 	that tthe website is reachable via that port
Fix SELinux context /var/www/html, it needed 
	semanage port -a -t http_port_t -p tcp 85
	semanage port -l | grep http

	firewall-cmd --add-port=85/tcp --permanent
	firewall-cmf --reload

